The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: The country?s trade deficit shot up by more than 79 per cent to $17.4-billion during April to August against $9.7 billion a year ago. According to official data, exports recorded a robust growth of 25 per cent at $7.3 billion in August. However, this was outstripped by a 32.44 per cent surge in imports during the month at $10.5 billion. Exports during the first five months grew 23 per cent at over $45.7 billion, while imports were up 37.07 per cent at $53.1 billion.

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: Alarmed at the influx of a huge amount of fake currency notes, the Reserve Bank has filed a complaint with Delhi police and directed all commercial banks to be more vigilant. In the last four months, the RBI had received counterfeit notes, having a face value of Rs 3.5 lakh, from commercial banks.

 Mumbai, Sept. 13: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL), headed by Mukesh Ambani, has moved Bombay High Court seeking its stamp of approval on the de-merger scheme of the Reliance empire. The petition will come up for hearing on September 16.

 Calcutta, Sept. 13: CESC Ltd has allotted 10 lakh warrants each to two promoter group companies, Universal Industrial Fund Ltd and Petrochem International Ltd.

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: VSNL has filed a petition before the TDSAT, challenging telecom regulator Trai?s order on international bandwidth. It has also questioned Trai?s assessment and methodology of costs for international bandwidth and the rationale for regulating prices in that field.

 Mumbai, Sept. 13: An independent commission today opposed consolidation in public sector banks, saying it would result in financial fragility due to increased exposure to sensitive sectors such as commodities, real estate and capital markets.

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: CDMA operators have sought three months? time to comply with the government order on treating fixed wireless phones as WiLL(M).




